Health effects are of course related to the biological component of atmospheric aerosol (bioaerosol) too. From the pioneer investigations at the end of the nineteenth century [36], the study of primary biological aerosol particles (PBAP) has become a multidisciplinary field of research where fungal spores and bacteria play an important role [37, 38]. Bacteria concentration in the outdoor atmosphere ranges from 104\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
