Fine particles (i.e. the PM2.5 fraction) are most effective in scattering the visible light: the maximum scattering cross section per unit mass, per several materials present in the atmospheric aerosols, falls in the range 0.7λ<D<2.2λ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
